headline: Can Humana Beat Q2 Earnings Estimates on Insurance Unit Strength?
summary: HUM's second-quarter earnings are likely to have witnessed strength in insurance premiums and Medicare, partly offset by rising costs and membership declines.

headline: Health insurance companies have a problem — people are using their plans more
summary: As Americans use their health insurance more and the cost of care increases, insurance companies have seen their financial results come under pressure.
